The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, March 9: National carrier Air India is expected to suffer a loss of about Rs 5,400 crore during 2009-10 and the trend of losses is likely to continue for a few more years, civil aviation minister Praful Patel said in the Rajya Sabha today. The total loss suffered by the airline in the past three financial years is likely to reach Rs 13,174.16 crore. The airlines suffered a loss of Rs 5,548 crore during 2008-09.                             
	 New Delhi, March 9: The Lok Sabha today passed the railways demand for grants and appropriation bill for 2010-11 without any discussion, amidst protests against the Womens Reservation Bill. The measures meant for the first three months of 2010-11 were also adopted.                             
	 New Delhi, March 9: The government expects inflation to cool down by April with the winter-sown crop boosting food supplies. Headline inflation measured by the wholesale price index is likely to average 4 per cent in the financial year through March 31, chief economic adviser Kaushik Basu said.                            
	 New Delhi, March 9: Sony India will invest up to Rs 1,800 crore in the next one year to market and promote activities to create awareness about its products in India.                             
	 Bangalore, March 9: Business solutions provider Aditya Birla Minacs has acquired UK-based Compass BPO, a finance and accounting services firm.                                                                                                                          
